11 that the person individual be discharged immediately.
12 (2) For a petition filed under section 434, if the court finds
13 that an individual is found to be a person requiring treatment, the
14 court shall do 1 of the following:
15 (a) Order the individual hospitalized in a hospital
16 recommended by the community mental health services program or
17 other entity as designated by the department.
18 (b) Order the individual hospitalized in a private or veterans
19 administration Veterans Administration hospital at the request of
20 the individual or his or her the individual's family, if private or
21 federal funds are to will be utilized and if the hospital agrees.
22 If the individual is hospitalized in a private or Veterans
23 Administration hospital under this subdivision, any a financial
24 obligation for the hospitalization shall must be satisfied from
25 funding sources other than the community mental health services
26 program, the department, or other state or county funding.
27 (c) Order the individual to undergo a program of combined
28 hospitalization and assisted outpatient treatment, as recommended
29 by the community mental health services program or other entity as
