15 community mental health services program or other entity as
16 designated by the department does not communicate with the court
17 regarding the treatment of the individual receiving assisted
18 outpatient treatment, the court shall hold a hearing regarding the
19 treatment provided to the individual receiving assisted outpatient
20 treatment by the community mental health services program or other
21 entity as designated by the department. Except as otherwise
22 provided in this subdivision, the court order may include a case
23 management plan and case management services and 1 or more of the
24 following:
25 (i) Medication.
26 (ii) Blood or urinalysis tests to determine compliance with or
27 effectiveness of prescribed medication.
28 (iii) Individual or group therapy, or both.
29 (iv) Day or partial day programs.
